WEBVTT

00:20.354 --> 00:22.148
[Pat] Previously on
Shining Vale...

00:22.314 --> 00:24.775
When your mom and I saw it,
we fell in love with it.

00:24.942 --> 00:27.445
[Pat] It's 100 miles away from
all the crazy in the city.

00:27.570 --> 00:29.447
How many fucking possessed
women do you get in here?

00:29.613 --> 00:31.615
Rosemary, get the fuck
out of my house.

00:31.782 --> 00:33.617
This is for you, Patricia.

00:33.784 --> 00:35.828
[Pat] The neighbor killed
herself on our fence.

00:35.995 --> 00:37.371
[Rosemary] I want to throw
a party.

00:37.538 --> 00:39.123
[Pat] We can invite
all of our new friends.

00:39.290 --> 00:41.000
-I'm Claire Vanderbilt.
-This is Laird.

00:41.125 --> 00:44.128
I'm so sorry I peed your floor.
Please have me back.

00:44.295 --> 00:46.297
You are the worst
therapist ever!

00:46.422 --> 00:48.716
Gaynor, tell them
I'm not crazy!

00:48.883 --> 00:51.427
-The electric shock treatment.
-[screams]

00:51.594 --> 00:53.721
You zapped Rosemary
right out of me.

00:53.888 --> 00:55.973
Jake and I don't need you
and Dad doesn't remember you.

00:56.140 --> 00:57.141
[screams]

00:57.308 --> 00:58.350
I don't play VR anymore.

00:58.517 --> 00:59.477
[Fred]
You still scared of that girl?

00:59.602 --> 01:01.145
What game?
I'm Daisy.

01:01.312 --> 01:03.522
I'm gonna be
the best wife and mother.

01:03.689 --> 01:05.149
That's what you'll talk about
on the book tour.

01:05.316 --> 01:06.817
[Pat] What, you already
published it?

01:06.942 --> 01:09.737
[Gaynor] How do I know you're
not gonna go batshit again?

01:09.904 --> 01:13.574
Because I am in control.

01:13.741 --> 01:15.159
I am in...

01:15.326 --> 01:16.702
[distorted neighing]

01:16.869 --> 01:19.121
Hello, dear.
So good to see you.

01:19.246 --> 01:22.249
[eerie music playing]

01:22.416 --> 01:23.334
Fuck.

01:24.794 --> 01:26.337
-[heartbeat thumping]
-Oh, my God.

01:26.504 --> 01:28.255
Oh, my God, oh, my God,
oh, my God, oh, my God.

01:28.380 --> 01:29.590
Oh, my God, oh, my God.

01:29.715 --> 01:31.133
♪ ♪

01:31.300 --> 01:33.259
[groans]

01:33.426 --> 01:35.387
Oh, my God, oh, my God,
oh, my God.

01:35.513 --> 01:37.515
[indistinct chatter]

01:37.681 --> 01:38.933
Gaynor, can I talk to you
just for a sec?

01:39.098 --> 01:40.559
What's the matter--why are you
breathing like Roxy?

01:40.684 --> 01:42.686
Because I need to go to--

01:42.853 --> 01:44.146
[Terry] Need to go where, Pat?

01:44.271 --> 01:47.107
[tense music plays]

01:47.274 --> 01:48.442
Get ice cream.

01:48.609 --> 01:49.902
-[Jake] Yes!
-[Terry] Road trip!

01:50.069 --> 01:51.195
Let's do it.

01:51.362 --> 01:53.405
-Hi. I have a return.
-[Pat] It's not a return.

01:53.531 --> 01:55.366
I just need a quick
outpatient shock treatment.

01:55.491 --> 01:56.741
Uh, sorry. We don't do that.

01:56.866 --> 01:59.036
Gaynor, why don't you go
find your dad and brother?

01:59.203 --> 02:00.955
Mommy's gonna talk to the nurse
for just a second.

02:01.121 --> 02:04.792
Mm, maybe Mommy could've driven
herself to the mental hospital.

02:04.959 --> 02:06.335
Listen, I don't think
you understand.

02:06.502 --> 02:09.213
I'm in a serious crisis.
I just need a quick zap.

02:09.338 --> 02:11.048
-I'll be out of your hair.
-That's not how it works.

02:11.215 --> 02:13.884
-Do you know who I am?
-Yes. You're Patricia Phelps.

02:14.051 --> 02:15.094
Your insurance ran out

02:15.261 --> 02:16.220
and you're no longer
a patient here.

02:16.387 --> 02:18.597
What, am I not
crazy enough for you, huh?

02:18.722 --> 02:20.432
What do you want me to do, huh?
Do you want me to...

02:20.599 --> 02:21.725
[trilling]

02:21.892 --> 02:23.227
You want me to take a shit
on the floor?

02:23.352 --> 02:25.145
The state no longer
considers that insane,

02:25.312 --> 02:26.605
but go for it.

02:28.190 --> 02:29.608
[buzzer buzzes]

02:29.775 --> 02:32.903
[Gussie] I'm not crazy!
I'm not crazy!

02:33.070 --> 02:34.154
I'm not!

02:34.321 --> 02:35.239
I am.

02:35.406 --> 02:36.740
[Jake] Dad, I'm scared.

02:36.906 --> 02:38.075
She's gonna be fine.

02:38.242 --> 02:40.578
No, I mean, the ice cream place
closes at 9:00.

02:40.744 --> 02:41.996
We're not gonna make it.

02:42.162 --> 02:45.332
Shh, let's not miss out
on this chance to bond.

02:45.499 --> 02:48.502
What kind of dad was I? Hmm?

02:48.668 --> 02:50.629
Honestly, Dad,

02:50.796 --> 02:52.423
right now, I'm just

02:52.590 --> 02:54.341
trying not to rip
this chair out of the floor

02:54.508 --> 02:55.759
and throw it
through that window.

02:55.926 --> 02:57.219
I'm gonna walk around.

03:01.098 --> 03:03.767
[eerie music plays]

03:03.934 --> 03:05.603
♪ ♪

03:05.769 --> 03:06.687
Hi.

03:06.854 --> 03:09.857
♪ ♪

03:10.024 --> 03:11.817
Okay.

03:16.488 --> 03:19.366
[suspenseful music plays]

03:19.533 --> 03:20.534
♪ ♪

03:20.701 --> 03:22.995
[mouthing words]

03:23.120 --> 03:25.706
[electricity zapping]

03:28.250 --> 03:29.627
[mouthing words]

03:31.462 --> 03:34.089
Let's go. Total bust.

03:34.214 --> 03:36.216
Apparently, I'm not crazy
enough for this place anymore.

03:36.383 --> 03:37.885
[Jake] I hope you're crazy
enough to drive full speed

03:38.010 --> 03:39.637
into the mall,
because in one minute,

03:39.803 --> 03:41.013
the ice cream store closes.

03:41.180 --> 03:42.264
Fuck.
We're not getting ice cream.

03:42.430 --> 03:43.390
We have ice cream at home.

03:43.557 --> 03:45.517
It's not the same
and you know it!

03:48.562 --> 03:51.398
[eerie musical sting]

03:51.565 --> 03:54.526
♪ ♪

04:07.706 --> 04:08.999
[Pat] Gaynor, let's go.

04:11.168 --> 04:12.920
I don't know why I get excited
about anything.

04:13.045 --> 04:16.089
-Almost. It's Phelps.
-[both] We are Phelps.

04:16.255 --> 04:19.677
[all] We are Phelps.
We are Phelps.

04:19.843 --> 04:20.761
They're amazing.

04:20.886 --> 04:22.846
I hate this place.

04:23.013 --> 04:24.473
[all] We are Phelps.

04:24.640 --> 04:27.476
[eerie music plays]

04:27.601 --> 04:30.437
♪ ♪

04:37.695 --> 04:39.571
[buzzer buzzes]

04:39.697 --> 04:42.324
[Gaynor] Jake, I'm tired of
washing your sheets every day.

04:42.449 --> 04:44.118
Either do your own laundry
or put a sock on it.

04:44.284 --> 04:45.869
I am a growing boy.

04:46.036 --> 04:47.162
Yeah, well, grow into a tissue.

04:47.329 --> 04:49.123
Hey, Jake, help me out here.

04:49.289 --> 04:51.500
I'm trying to read
your mom's book.

04:51.667 --> 04:53.460
Ever since the accident,
I still have problems

04:53.627 --> 04:56.797
with abstract word fractions
like--look at this.

04:56.922 --> 04:58.298
I'm not allowed to read that.

04:58.465 --> 05:00.634
[sighs]
Well, your dad says you can.

05:00.801 --> 05:03.595
"The mailman obli-ged..."

05:03.762 --> 05:06.056
That's obliged.
The G is like a J.

05:06.223 --> 05:08.183
Okay. All right. There you go.

05:08.308 --> 05:12.229
"The mailmen obliged
and fin-jer ban-jed..."

05:12.396 --> 05:15.899
Okay, um, that's fingerbanged.

05:16.066 --> 05:17.484
-[Terry] Say it again.
-[Jake] Fingerbanged.

05:17.651 --> 05:19.153
-[Terry] Say it again.
-Fingerbanged.

05:19.319 --> 05:20.404
-I hate this.
-Well, no.

05:20.571 --> 05:21.572
We're father-son bonding.

05:21.697 --> 05:23.574
"He fingerbanged
her tig-hit snatch."

05:23.741 --> 05:24.575
[Jake] Okay, I'm leaving.

05:24.742 --> 05:27.077
Hey, sorry I overslept.

05:27.244 --> 05:28.328
Did I miss breakfast?

05:28.454 --> 05:29.705
Twice. It's Thursday.

05:29.872 --> 05:32.916
I slept for two days
and no one checked on me?

05:33.082 --> 05:34.585
I'm sorry, I was a little busy
taking care

05:34.752 --> 05:36.086
of your newborn husband
and your son

05:36.253 --> 05:37.838
who's turning his laundry
into sheetrock.

05:37.963 --> 05:39.923
Hey, being a mascot
is stressful.

05:40.090 --> 05:41.842
You try walking a mile
in my fuzzy shoes.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.635
I'm sorry, honey,
I wanted to check on you,

05:43.802 --> 05:45.429
but I'm still having a problem
with the stairs,

05:45.596 --> 05:47.306
and the electric chair
wasn't working.

05:47.431 --> 05:48.682
The electric chair?

05:48.849 --> 05:51.935
The chair that helps you get
up and down the back steps.

05:52.102 --> 05:53.103
Back steps?

05:53.270 --> 05:54.563
Jesus Christ,
we have an electric chair

05:54.688 --> 05:56.398
that gets old people upstairs.

05:58.776 --> 06:00.069
-[Pat] Gaynor.
-Yeah?

06:00.194 --> 06:01.361
-You don't have to do this.
-[Gaynor] No, I can do it.

06:01.528 --> 06:02.321
It's not your job.
I'll take it.

06:02.488 --> 06:03.322
No, I can do it. No, leave it.

06:03.489 --> 06:04.615
[Pat] Come on. Give it to me.

06:04.782 --> 06:06.283
-Give it to me.
-Leave it.

06:06.450 --> 06:07.743
[Pat] Oh, my God,
what is wrong with you?

06:07.910 --> 06:09.119
[Gaynor groans]

06:09.286 --> 06:12.498
You happy?
You broke Jake's pillowcase.

06:12.664 --> 06:16.877
Jake, you've got to be careful
with your VR headset.

06:17.044 --> 06:19.922
I didn't put that there.
I don't play with that anymore.

06:20.089 --> 06:21.632
All right,
will everybody relax?

06:21.799 --> 06:22.841
I'm sorry,
we all don't have the luxury

06:23.008 --> 06:23.842
of sleeping for two days.

06:24.009 --> 06:25.177
No one woke me up.

06:25.344 --> 06:26.804
I'm not your alarm clock, Mom.

06:26.970 --> 06:28.097
Okay, you know,
I'm your mother.

06:28.222 --> 06:29.348
-[Terry] Hey.
-I respect your stuff.

06:29.473 --> 06:30.891
-[overlapping argument]
-[Terry] Hey!

06:31.016 --> 06:32.601
[cane banging]

06:34.103 --> 06:36.605
As the leader of this family,
I've made a decision.

06:36.772 --> 06:38.232
We need professional help.

06:38.357 --> 06:40.651
I'm gonna get us to the best
doctor we can afford.

06:40.818 --> 06:43.529
I have to admit,
I'm a bit surprised

06:43.695 --> 06:44.988
to hear from you, Terry.

06:45.155 --> 06:47.407
You were in my phone under
"cheap therapist."

06:47.574 --> 06:49.243
Terry fell down the stairs
and suffered

06:49.409 --> 06:52.371
a traumatic brain injury
and lost his memory.

06:52.538 --> 06:53.664
Ah, I see.

06:53.831 --> 06:55.207
Yeah, and then this one
went batshit,

06:55.374 --> 06:56.917
leaving me to clean up
their mess.

06:57.084 --> 06:58.377
That's our story.

06:58.544 --> 07:01.839
Actually, the epilogue is,
I'm home and I am healthy.

07:01.964 --> 07:03.590
And the sequel is,
I had to drive her back

07:03.757 --> 07:05.134
to the mental hospital
two days ago.

07:05.300 --> 07:07.928
And the reboot is, I was
too healthy to be let back in.

07:08.053 --> 07:10.556
Guys, please.
He's a professional.

07:10.722 --> 07:12.349
We paid a lot of money
to hear from him.

07:12.516 --> 07:13.976
Please, Doctor.

07:14.143 --> 07:15.602
Thank you, Terry.

07:15.769 --> 07:18.772
You've all been through
a lifetime's worth of trauma.

07:18.939 --> 07:22.151
Healing as a family requires
a lot of individual work

07:22.276 --> 07:23.318
-and patience.
-Screw that.

07:23.485 --> 07:25.195
Listen, something's happened
to my memory,

07:25.362 --> 07:27.197
and I need it back now.

07:27.364 --> 07:29.032
-That's not an ashtray.
-I don't mind.

07:29.199 --> 07:33.036
Something disturbing
happened in my past.

07:33.203 --> 07:35.789
-I feel like it's right here...
-[flesh squelching]

07:35.956 --> 07:38.041
...and I can't get to it.

07:38.207 --> 07:39.626
What about art therapy?

07:39.793 --> 07:43.714
Painting allows people with
physical and verbal challenges

07:43.881 --> 07:47.217
access to thoughts,
emotions, and fears

07:47.384 --> 07:49.720
they can't otherwise express.

07:49.887 --> 07:52.389
I've had quite a bit
of success at it.

07:52.514 --> 07:55.183
[creepy musical stings]

07:55.308 --> 07:56.602
♪ ♪

07:56.727 --> 07:58.353
I'm sorry. Can we go?

07:58.520 --> 07:59.980
I'm the only one in this family
with a job,

08:00.147 --> 08:01.398
and I can't afford
to get fired.

08:01.565 --> 08:03.150
No one asked you
to quit school.

08:03.275 --> 08:04.985
Well, I have to take care
of this family.

08:05.152 --> 08:08.405
That's a big job for a girl.
Or even a boy.

08:08.572 --> 08:12.242
You have to find a way
to resolve that stress,

08:12.409 --> 08:15.412
or it can lead to long-term
psychological damage.

08:15.537 --> 08:18.957
Your mother is a fine example
of trauma run amok.

08:19.124 --> 08:21.084
Ah, thanks for those genes,
Mom.

08:21.251 --> 08:23.545
Okay, well, I also gave you
my thigh gap, so...

08:23.712 --> 08:26.798
Obviously there's some
mother-daughter issues at play.

08:26.965 --> 08:28.508
No, I don't have any issues.

08:28.675 --> 08:31.345
I just want to go back to being
a loving wife and mother.

08:31.511 --> 08:34.514
Why don't you try something
you're good at instead?

08:34.681 --> 08:35.765
[laughs]
Good one.

08:35.933 --> 08:38.101
Button, let's be respectful
to our mother.

08:38.268 --> 08:39.602
She's an amazing woman.

08:39.770 --> 08:41.438
[Dr. Berg] Everybody in
this family needs a break.

08:41.605 --> 08:44.066
Reward yourself
with something you enjoy.

08:44.232 --> 08:45.442
You- you're a writer. Do that.

08:45.609 --> 08:47.486
No writer enjoys writing.

08:47.653 --> 08:50.489
Besides, my book is finished.

08:50.656 --> 08:53.450
I guess I could promote it,
but...

08:53.617 --> 08:56.161
I really want to focus
on this family.

08:56.328 --> 08:57.204
Anyone here in favor of that?

08:57.371 --> 08:58.705
-Fuck no.
-No thanks.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.624
-I'll call Kam on the way home.
-Outstanding.

09:00.791 --> 09:02.626
What about you,
my furry friend?

09:02.793 --> 09:03.794
Sometimes the youngest
in the family

09:03.961 --> 09:04.962
gets lost in the shuffle.

09:05.128 --> 09:08.924
Now is your time
to be seen and heard.

09:09.091 --> 09:11.218
[soft dramatic music plays]

09:11.343 --> 09:14.096
Last year, there was this...

09:14.263 --> 09:17.391
girl in my VR headset, and...

09:17.557 --> 09:21.144
she was, like, trying to get me
to do something--

09:21.311 --> 09:23.438
Well, get used to that.

09:23.563 --> 09:26.733
-[watch beeps]
-Ah, that's our time, Phelps.

09:26.858 --> 09:28.068
He's good.

09:30.445 --> 09:33.365
♪ ♪

09:35.867 --> 09:37.160
[dramatic musical sting]

09:37.286 --> 09:38.328
[gasps]

09:38.495 --> 09:39.371
Hello, dear.

09:39.496 --> 09:41.331
Get the fuck out of my house.

09:41.498 --> 09:44.209
Honey, are you okay?

09:45.669 --> 09:46.670
Yeah. Why do you ask?

09:46.837 --> 09:49.339
You're screaming
at our neighbor.

09:49.506 --> 09:51.633
-Hi.
-Hi, Ter.

09:54.469 --> 09:56.096
You see her?

09:56.263 --> 09:57.264
Yeah.
[chuckles]

09:57.431 --> 09:58.515
[chuckles]

09:58.640 --> 10:01.351
I let her in.
Pat, this is Ruth.

10:01.518 --> 10:02.436
[Ruth] Levin.

10:02.602 --> 10:04.813
I- I just bought
the house next door.

10:04.980 --> 10:07.774
Apparently, the former owner,
she committed suicide.

10:07.941 --> 10:09.443
-What are you gonna do?
-[doorbell rings]

10:09.609 --> 10:11.361
Oh, that's for me.

10:11.528 --> 10:13.530
Guy named Lard called.

10:13.697 --> 10:16.116
Said he's my best friend.
I don't know.

10:16.241 --> 10:17.617
Ter-bear, think fast.

10:19.536 --> 10:21.038
I just don't have it yet. I--

10:21.204 --> 10:22.998
No, no.
You're-you're getting better.

10:23.123 --> 10:24.875
[Terry] No, I'm not.

10:28.670 --> 10:30.213
What are you doing here?

10:30.380 --> 10:32.674
Well, like I said,
I'm just, you know,

10:32.799 --> 10:35.052
doing a little juicing
for Terry and the kids.

10:35.218 --> 10:38.013
I'm just trying to help out
a little bit around here.

10:38.180 --> 10:39.473
Are you okay?

10:39.639 --> 10:42.559
♪ ♪

10:46.980 --> 10:47.981
You're real.

10:50.567 --> 10:52.110
You're real too.

10:52.277 --> 10:54.237
I used to know someone
who looked just like you.

10:54.404 --> 10:55.489
Isn't that funny?

10:55.655 --> 10:58.450
I- I was thinking
you look so familiar too.

10:58.575 --> 10:59.576
Are you from Brooklyn?

10:59.701 --> 11:01.244
Everyone in Connecticut
is from Brooklyn.

11:01.411 --> 11:03.747
Okay, so did you walk your dog
in Prospect Park?

11:03.914 --> 11:04.998
No.

11:05.165 --> 11:06.249
Did you possess me in my attic?

11:06.416 --> 11:07.834
No.

11:07.959 --> 11:09.544
Hold on. We'll get it.

11:09.711 --> 11:11.922
All right, so it couldn't be
Rizzo's Butcher

11:12.089 --> 11:15.008
because I was
a vegetarian back then.

11:15.175 --> 11:17.594
So we never met there.

11:17.719 --> 11:19.388
And it's not Murray's Cheese

11:19.554 --> 11:22.140
because I was
lactose intolerant.

11:22.307 --> 11:24.017
[gasps]
Oh, June Cleaver.

11:24.184 --> 11:25.435
-What?
-[Ruth] Ah.

11:25.602 --> 11:28.647
You were in
a prenatal yoga class

11:28.814 --> 11:30.524
about 17 years ago.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.859
-Cobble Hill Kundalini.
-[Pat] Yeah.

11:33.026 --> 11:34.861
-[Ruth] Yes.
-I only went twice.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.446
I went on the regular.

11:36.613 --> 11:38.615
I mean, in fact,
I did absolutely everything

11:38.782 --> 11:40.033
Dr. Spock recommended,

11:40.200 --> 11:42.327
which really bugged
the crap out of you.

11:42.452 --> 11:46.790
I remember one day, I said
that having a baby

11:46.957 --> 11:49.668
was what my whole life
was leading up to.

11:49.793 --> 11:51.128
And then you called me
June Cleaver

11:51.294 --> 11:53.755
and everyone laughed,
except me.

11:53.922 --> 11:56.633
-I found it hurtful.
-Oh, my God.

11:56.758 --> 11:59.428
Last year, I was

11:59.594 --> 12:03.014
tormented by this imaginary
'50s housewife.

12:03.140 --> 12:05.142
You must've made
a real impression on me,

12:05.267 --> 12:07.352
because she had your face.

12:07.519 --> 12:09.646
Oh, I don't know
what to do with that.

12:09.813 --> 12:11.731
[Pat] Nothing.

12:11.857 --> 12:15.402
I just met the face
of my mental illness.

12:15.569 --> 12:18.613
Ah. Well, do me a favor, dear.

12:18.738 --> 12:21.908
Will you hand
your mental illness that knife?

12:22.033 --> 12:24.744
Oh, yeah.

12:24.911 --> 12:26.496
-[Ruth] Thank you.
-Wow.

12:28.498 --> 12:30.333
So if you were
in that yoga class,

12:30.500 --> 12:32.419
you must have a kid
Gaynor's age.

12:32.586 --> 12:34.588
It is the worst, right?

12:34.713 --> 12:37.424
Well, my Leo's an angel.

12:37.591 --> 12:40.927
Oh, well, you're lucky.
My Gaynor is--she hates me.

12:41.094 --> 12:43.472
I mean, my Leo's an angel.

12:43.638 --> 12:45.765
-He was stillborn.
-Oh.

